folder: Stanton Street & Orchard Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Stanton Street, north side, east from (No. 84), and including Orchard Street.

April 30, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

Peddlers--foodstuffs and clothing: A series of three views showing various aspects of the Orchard St. pushcart market. Mayor LaGuardia is sponsoring a new enclosed City Market on Essex Street to replace this. Opening of same will occur in January of 1940 and a municipal ordinance enforced against pushcarting. These views, taken at Stanton and Orchard Streets, were published in the Guide Series of the W. P. A.

W. P. A. Federal Writers Project
